Trying to solve for shortest: Ruby (42)
gets.split.map{|s|print s[-1]*s.chop.to_i}

If the last character of each block cannot be a numerical digit, this shortens to 37
gets.split.map{|s|print s[-1]*s.to_i}

When Ruby 2.6 is out, these will become 38 and 33 respectively
gets.split{|s|print s[-1]*s.chop.to_i}

Note that these also break if spaces are allowed as decorations, though since the statement says the blocks are "space separated" I assume space decorations are disallowed.
